to me.

20:34.276 --> 20:35.903
Did you know that?

20:35.986 --> 20:37.279
Stop it! Hey!

20:37.362 --> 20:39.281
- Stop, you idiot!
- Hey!

20:39.364 --> 20:40.490
Stop!

20:41.533 --> 20:43.035
- Hey!
- Stop!

20:43.118 --> 20:44.786
- That's enough.
- Stop it.

20:44.870 --> 20:47.039
- Stop it. I said stop it.
- Stop it! Stop!

20:47.122 --> 20:48.665
That is enough! Stop it!

20:48.749 --> 20:51.001
That is enough.

20:51.084 --> 20:52.836
- Fuck off!
- What did you say?

20:53.879 --> 20:54.963
No!

20:55.047 --> 20:57.090
You will not be like him!

20:57.174 --> 20:58.174
You...

21:00.010 --> 21:01.511
Max, I'm sorry.

21:01.595 --> 21:04.097
Maxie? Maxie, I'm sorry.

21:05.891 --> 21:06.891
I'm sorry.

21:06.934 --> 21:08.852
Mom.

21:08.936 --> 21:10.854
Oh, my God.

21:10.938 --> 21:12.189
Josh, come here.

21:13.732 --> 21:15.943
Are you all right? Huh?

21:16.777 --> 21:17.777
Are you okay?

21:27.412 --> 21:28.538
You smell that?

21:29.581 --> 21:31.458
Clears your sinuses right out.

21:32.834 --> 21:36.213
We have all this newfangled stuff
to improve ourselves.

21:37.631 --> 21:40.300
Self-help apps all over our phones.

21:41.343 --> 21:47.516
Sometimes all we need to do
is just stand still and breathe.

21:47.599 --> 21:51.520
To just breathe in the air
that's all around us.

21:51.603 --> 21:53.230
Is that for me, Mama?

21:54.773 --> 21:56.817
You want me to breathe better?

22:02.155 --> 22:06.243
- Tell me what's going on, Bonnie.
- Nothing, Nathan's just tripping.

22:06.326 --> 22:09.121
Nathan is a complete dolt.

22:09.204 --> 22:12.082
When it comes to emotional,
social intelligence,

22:12.165 --> 22:15.127
oh, Bonnie, he's as dumb as a rock.

22:16.420 --> 22:20.590
But I often wonder
if that's why you married him.

22:20.674 --> 22:24.136
You are out here surrounded by people
who don't even get you.

22:24.219 --> 22:26.138
They don't look like you.

22:26.221 --> 22:29.725
I haven't seen one other black person
since I've been out here.

22:29.808 --> 22:31.935
Is that why you're here?

22:32.019 --> 22:36.940
I mean, because we all know
how fond you are of your walls.

22:37.024 --> 22:38.483
You are out of control.

22:40.527 --> 22:44.114
Something's in the air, Bonnie.
And I don't like it.

22:50.412 --> 22:52.706
You know, I decided to run.

22:54.458 --> 22:55.500
For office?

22:56.835 --> 22:59.504
I swear to fucking God, man.
No, I decided to take up running

22:59.588 --> 23:02.340
because Bonnie likes running.
She's obsessed with it.

23:02.424 --> 23:05.677
- I'm trying to embrace her interests.
- So I'm off the hook for lunch, then?

23:05.761 --> 23:09.347
You remember what you said to me
last year about "give me a reason"?

23:09.431 --> 23:11.850
Should we just get this
out of our system, man?

23:13.268 --> 23:15.979
Okay, so you've asked me
to have lunch with your wife,

23:16.063 --> 23:19.775
and now you challenge me to a fistfight.

23:19.858 --> 23:23.612
I mean, do you have a preference
if I can't squeeze in both?

23:25.614 --> 23:26.615
Really?

23:27.657 --> 23:30.160
- So that's a no, huh?
- Okay.

23:30.243 --> 23:32.370
- Don't, buddy. Don't.
- Okay.

23:32.454 --> 23:33.454
Warning.

23:37.167 --> 23:42.255
Case 6273.
<i>United States v. Gordon Klein.</i>

23:42.339 --> 23:45.467
James Taylor on behalf of the
United States, Your Honor.

23:48.804 --> 23:52.891
Steve Gardner on behalf of Mr. Klein,
Your Honor. Plead not guilty.

23:56.937 --> 23:58.980
Mr. Klein.

23:59.064 --> 24:02.734
You're being charged with security fraud,
mail fraud and wire fraud,

24:02.818 --> 24:07.572
violating Section 17A
of the Securities Act of 1933

24:07.656 --> 24:11.618
and Rule 105
of Regulation M of the Exchange Act.

24:12.994 --> 24:14.454
Question of bail?

24:14.538 --> 24:15.831
No priors, judge.

24:15.914 --> 24:20.919
I ask that the defendant post bail
in excess of $1 million

24:21.002 --> 24:23.421
in light of the severity of the charge.

24:23.505 --> 24:25.757
One million sounds excessive.

24:25.841 --> 24:27.634
One million bond.

24:27.717 --> 24:30.011
Five hundred thousand dollars cash...

24:30.095 --> 24:31.346
Stop!

24:32.764 --> 24:35.851
We'll conference on Tuesday
to set a schedule.

24:35.934 --> 24:38.478
- Thank you, Your Honor.
- Thank you.

24:47.279 --> 24:49.447
I swear someone's gonna do a start-up,

24:49.531 --> 24:52.159
and they're gonna make,
like, the perfect French fry.

24:52.242 --> 24:56.121
It's gonna be, like, nutritional
and healthy and no cal.

24:56.204 --> 24:57.372
It's gonna be a gold mine.

24:57.455 --> 25:00.375
Remember when you used to call them
pomp freaks?

25:00.458 --> 25:01.543
Mm-hm.

25:02.252 --> 25:03.128
French fries.

25:03.211 --> 25:06.131
When she was little,
I told her they were called <i>pommes frites,</i>

25:06.214 --> 25:09.551
and then she started calling them
pomp freaks.

25:09.634 --> 25:12.429
I never even noticed
you eating a French fry.

25:12.512 --> 25:13.680
I eat French fries.

25:13.763 --> 25:15.974
Yeah, you're right.
You just didn't notice, did you?

25:16.057 --> 25:17.601
That's your thing, isn't it?

25:18.643 --> 25:20.896
- Wait, what?
- Don't get all sensitive with yourself.

25:20.979 --> 25:22.814
I'm not. I'm not being sensitive.

25:22.898 --> 25:24.482
- I'm just... What do you mean?
- Honey?

25:27.068 --> 25:28.653
No, I notice things.

25:29.613 --> 25:30.739
I mean...

25:30.822 --> 25:34.451
Like, I noticed shit,
and then I asked you to come.

25:34.534 --> 25:36.036
- So...
- Well, I'm here...

25:37.370 --> 25:39.915
because you're ill-equipped
to connect with your wife.

25:44.336 --> 25:46.504
- Mom, you're drinking again.
- No.

25:47.589 --> 25:50.926
I mean, it's just one glass. Occasionally.

25:51.009 --> 25:52.510
One glass is fine.

25:53.595 --> 25:55.055
One hundred, not so much.

25:55.138 --> 25:56.389
Those days are over.

25:57.474 --> 26:00.185
- Your problem is you're oblivious.
- Will you stop?

26:00.268 --> 26:03.396
You call me and you say
that something's wrong with Bonnie.

26:04.522 --> 26:05.941
"Bonnie's not herself."

26:07.025 --> 26:10.695
"Been going on six months
to a year or so."

26:13.073 --> 26:15.742
Can you narrow that down
a little bit further for me, Nathan?

26:15.825 --> 26:18.912
I mean, can you pinpoint a specific date?

26:18.995 --> 26:20.830
Instance. Anything?

26:21.873 --> 26:23.166
Because I can.

26:25.502 --> 26:26.836
It was after that event.

26:27.921 --> 26:30.715
You all went to that student gala.

26:30.799 --> 26:31.967
Where the man died.

26:33.343 --> 26:34.678
And Bonnie was there.

26:36.805 --> 26:38.807
Your wife watched a man
fall down the steps

26:38.890 --> 26:42.227
and bust his goddamn head open
and splatter all over the place and die.

26:43.520 --> 26:44.896
I don't know, from then to now,

26:44.980 --> 26:47.482
she's probably been dealing
with post-traumatic stress.

26:47.565 --> 26:49.150
I'm fine.

26:49.234 --> 26:51.486
- We're in a restaurant, honey.
- What does that mean?

26:51.569 --> 26:54.364
What, we should just glaze over it?
Act like everything is okay?

26:54.447 --> 26:57.075
Things are not okay.
Your daughter is not okay.

26:58.243 --> 27:01.913
And this mope-a-dope shit,
it clearly is not working for your husband.

27:01.997 --> 27:04.416
And I doubt very much
that it's working for your child.

27:04.499 --> 27:07.210
And from what I see,
it is not working for you.

27:07.294 --> 27:08.294
Mom.

27:12.799 --> 27:14.592
I'm really happy you're here.

27:18.430 --> 27:21.349
Can we just have a dinner
like a normal family?

27:21.433 --> 27:24.436
We are having dinner
like a normal family.

27:24.519 --> 27:27.981
Getting in each other's business, that's
what families do. That's why he called.

27:42.329 --> 27:44.497
<i>So you don't have any siblings?</i>

27:44.581 --> 27:45.749
<i>I had a brother.</i>

27:45.832 --> 27:47.208
Oh.

27:47.292 --> 27:49.669
He passed away when I was 5.

27:49.753 --> 27:51.171
Oh...

27:51.254 --> 27:52.547
Sorry about that.

27:52.630 --> 27:55.592
What about you?

27:58.303 --> 27:59.721
I'm an only child.

28:02.182 --> 28:04.517
- I mean, as far as I know.
- Oh, yeah?

28:04.601 --> 28:08.104
Yeah, I'm not very close to my dad, so...
Right?

28:09.439 --> 28:10.565
You never know.

28:12.442 --> 28:16.488
So your mom passed away,

28:16.571 --> 28:19.991
and you don't have any siblings,
as far as you know,

28:20.075 --> 28:22.619
and you don't talk much to your dad.

28:22.702 --> 28:23.703
Mm.

28:27.457 --> 28:30.126
Now, I don't mean to be presumptuous,
but...

28:31.836 --> 28:33.797
if this works out...

28:35.799 --> 28:37.759
I would have you all to myself.

28:49.229 --> 28:52.023
- Boys are tucked in.
- Thank you, Mary Louise.

28:52.107 --> 28:54.818
They must have been exhausted.
Max is asleep already.

28:56.236 --> 28:58.279
They tell me they have a brother.

28:59.614 --> 29:01.866
Evidently, Perry had a son.

29:01.950 --> 29:04.244
- What?
- With another woman.

29:04.327 --> 29:06.121
And the boy's in their class.

29:07.914 --> 29:09.916
Seems I have another grandchild.

29:12.293 --> 29:14.504
Might you have the decency to tell me...

29:15.630 --> 29:16.630
his name?

29:19.008 --> 29:21.136
- No.
<i>- Then how could they know?</i>

29:21.219 --> 29:23.638
I don't know.
You know what, we did tell that detective.

29:23.721 --> 29:25.682
- That bitch. She probably let it slip...
- Mom.

29:25.765 --> 29:29.894
I'm sorry. You know what, Celeste,
just find out what the boys know exactly

29:29.978 --> 29:32.063
<i>and then call me right back, okay? Bye.</i>

29:33.148 --> 29:34.858
What now?

29:34.941 --> 29:37.068
Celeste, just stuff with the twins, and...

29:37.152 --> 29:39.446
Did they find out Ziggy's their brother?

29:39.529 --> 29:40.655
Who told you that?

29:41.823 --> 29:43.616
I heard you talking on the phone once.

29:43.700 --> 29:44.951
Did you tell Max and Josh?

29:45.034 --> 29:48.496
Only that they have a brother
in the second grade.

29:48.580 --> 29:50.874
- Chloe, good God.
- I didn't say who.

29:50.957 --> 29:52.750
- Did you tell Ziggy this?
- Mm-hm.

29:52.834 --> 29:56.337
Wait, Perry Wright is Ziggy's father?

29:57.672 --> 29:59.757
- You know what, go to your room.
- I'm sorry.

29:59.841 --> 30:02.886
Give me your phone.
I'll deal with you later.

30:04.387 --> 30:06.473
<i>I'm so sorry. She's grounded.</i>

30:10.143 --> 30:12.061
- I gotta go.
<i>- Okay, I...</i>

30:13.396 --> 30:14.689
Oh, fuck.

30:14.772 --> 30:18.193
Hey. Talk for a sec?

30:18.276 --> 30:21.821
- What did I do?
- You didn't do anything. Um...

30:22.864 --> 30:25.783
Did Chloe Mackenzie say anything
to you about...

30:26.826 --> 30:28.495
About who your father is?

30:30.580 --> 30:32.999
She said it was Max and Josh's dad.

30:34.334 --> 30:35.334
Is it?

30:44.010 --> 30:45.261
Mm-hm.

30:47.889 --> 30:49.891
How long have you known for?

30:49.974 --> 30:51.518
Since August.

30:51.601 --> 30:55.146
Ziggy, you've known since August
and you haven't said anything to me?

30:56.397 --> 30:58.149
Figured you'd just lie.

31:00.860 --> 31:02.654
I didn't know.

31:02.737 --> 31:04.864
All of those years
of you asking me where he was

31:04.948 --> 31:06.449
or who he was, I...

31:07.700 --> 31:09.536
I didn't know who he was.

31:13.540 --> 31:16.668
I didn't know until Trivia Night.

31:16.751 --> 31:18.294
- And...
- But why didn't you tell me?

31:18.378 --> 31:20.338
Because I didn't know how.

31:21.464 --> 31:22.924
I just thought that I would wait.

31:24.384 --> 31:27.929
- Till when?
- Till you got older, I guess.

31:31.641 --> 31:33.685
Did Chloe tell you anything else?

31:35.895 --> 31:39.274
She said something about Mr. Wright
giving you salt.

31:39.357 --> 31:41.526
That's how I happened.

31:41.609 --> 31:43.027
He salted you.

31:54.205 --> 31:55.205
No.

32:04.924 --> 32:05.967
Then what did she mean?

32:07.260 --> 32:08.970
Can I sit down next to you?

32:18.313 --> 32:23.151
I think what Chloe overheard
was the word "assault."

32:27.780 --> 32:29.032
What does that mean?

32:43.546 --> 32:46.966
- Look, I wanted to tell you.
- Yeah, but you didn't.

32:47.050 --> 32:49.719
Well, I was trying to protect
Jane and Celeste's privacy.

32:49.802 --> 32:52.555
- But I'm your husband. Okay?
- Okay, but can you understand

32:52.639 --> 32:56.392
and maybe contemplate for a minute
the fundamental violation

32:56.476 --> 32:58.728
of a woman's privacy
when you're talking about rape?

32:58.811 --> 33:02.273
How about the fundamental violation
of our family, of our marriage.

33:02.357 --> 33:06.152
I mean, I'm your husband.
I am supposed to help you with this stuff.

33:06.235 --> 33:11.407
I mean, of course she's gonna hear you
whispering on the fucking phone, Madeline.

33:11.491 --> 33:14.118
I mean, look what our daughter did.

33:14.202 --> 33:17.997
What are we, people who keep secrets
from each other? Is that our thing now?

33:18.081 --> 33:19.123
Come on.

33:20.416 --> 33:21.626
Jesus.

33:26.756 --> 33:27.756
Mom?

33:29.258 --> 33:31.010
I'm really sorry again.

33:33.680 --> 33:36.057
I know you are, honey. I know.

33:37.100 --> 33:41.020
You can't tell your friends private things
that you've overheard us say on the phone.

33:42.105 --> 33:45.775
Okay?
No more eavesdropping, young lady.

33:45.858 --> 33:47.735
Is Daddy mad at me?

33:50.071 --> 33:51.447
Daddy's mad.

33:51.531 --> 33:53.741
But that's the thing about families,

33:53.825 --> 33:56.619
is that you can be mad and you can fight,

33:56.703 --> 33:59.539
but you get over it,
and you always come back together.

33:59.622 --> 34:01.708
That's what families do.

34:01.791 --> 34:03.835
- So we're gonna be okay.
- Okay.

34:06.212 --> 34:07.755
Can I have my phone back?

34:11.467 --> 34:14.594
So this thing
was supposed to have happened when?

34:14.679 --> 34:17.431
Like nine years ago?

34:17.514 --> 34:21.893
When you two were trying so hard
to have a baby? Please.

34:24.021 --> 34:26.940
When did you find out
about this alleged affair?

34:27.024 --> 34:30.485
It wasn't an affair. It was a rape. Rape.

34:30.570 --> 34:34.657
- When did you find out?
- The night he died.

34:39.245 --> 34:40.413
Then how can you...?

34:40.496 --> 34:44.292
This woman, she could have had
multiple partners, you know.

34:44.375 --> 34:47.754
She could have been drugged.
She... You don't know her.

34:47.837 --> 34:49.464
She could have been...

34:49.547 --> 34:51.591
What if she got it wrong?

34:51.674 --> 34:52.925
Aren't you desperate

34:53.009 --> 34:55.678
- She didn't.
- for her to be wrong?

34:55.762 --> 34:59.724
Aren't you desperate to know
that he wasn't unfaithful?

34:59.807 --> 35:04.312
To believe that he... He wasn't capable
of doing the things that she said.

35:05.605 --> 35:07.356
He wasn't.

35:07.440 --> 35:09.567
I'll never believe that.

35:09.650 --> 35:12.487
Your son wasn't an innocent man.
He beat me up.

35:12.570 --> 35:14.906
- I don't believe you.
- Many times. He...

35:14.989 --> 35:17.200
Why wouldn't you go to the police?

35:17.283 --> 35:20.912
- I probably should have.
- But you didn't.

35:20.995 --> 35:24.165
- No, because it wasn't simple.
- I don't believe you.

35:24.248 --> 35:26.751
I don't understand why you're so willing
to believe her.

35:26.834 --> 35:32.882
I don't know why you are willing
to assassinate his character, his memory,

35:32.965 --> 35:34.550
who he was.

35:34.634 --> 35:37.512
- What...? I...
- It's so hard.

35:37.595 --> 35:39.972
I'm telling you what it was.

35:40.056 --> 35:43.267
I'm not saying I was blameless.

35:43.351 --> 35:47.480
I'm just telling you
we were violent with each other,

35:47.563 --> 35:49.232
and sometimes...

35:52.276 --> 35:54.403
Sometimes it would lead to sex.

35:56.155 --> 35:58.032
I don't... I...

35:58.115 --> 35:59.700
We loved each other.

35:59.784 --> 36:02.036
- We were...
- But he beat you up.

36:04.163 --> 36:06.374
We had a sickness.

36:06.457 --> 36:08.459
And you didn't go to the police?

36:10.044 --> 36:11.044
I just...

36:12.380 --> 36:13.965
I'll go to the police.

36:15.424 --> 36:16.551
What?

36:16.634 --> 36:18.469
To get some answers.

36:18.553 --> 36:20.596
You left some things out, didn't you?

36:20.680 --> 36:24.267
The fact that he fathered another child.
You left that out.

36:24.350 --> 36:27.270
That you planned to move,
that you rented an apartment.

36:27.353 --> 36:28.563
You left that out.

36:30.565 --> 36:34.527
That you were planning to leave him
the very night he died.

36:34.610 --> 36:36.028
You left that out.

36:38.656 --> 36:40.408
And that you...

36:40.491 --> 36:45.872
You learned of his infidelity
just 10 seconds before he...

36:49.041 --> 36:52.336
went falling down a flight of stairs
to his death.

36:53.713 --> 36:56.340
Oh, you left that out too.

38:17.296 --> 38:18.422
How's Ziggy?

38:20.007 --> 38:21.007
He's, uh...

38:22.802 --> 38:23.802
I don't know.

38:24.845 --> 38:25.845
And you?

38:26.681 --> 38:29.308
Um, I gotta tell you something. I...

38:32.019 --> 38:33.980
I told Ziggy about the circumstances.

38:35.064 --> 38:36.691
The violence of it?

38:36.774 --> 38:38.150
Mm-hm.

38:38.234 --> 38:39.902
- What?
- Just a little bit, but he knows

38:39.986 --> 38:43.823
that he cannot share it with Max and Josh.
That it's just for him.

38:43.906 --> 38:46.242
- But we had an agreement.
- I know. I know.

38:46.325 --> 38:49.161
- We were gonna wait.
- I know, but I can't lie to him anymore.

38:49.245 --> 38:50.246
- I can't...
- No, I...

38:50.329 --> 38:52.206
- His entire life has just been built
- Jane.

38:52.289 --> 38:55.668
on a foundation of lies.
I can't just... I can't continue.

38:55.751 --> 38:57.795
And I know
that you have to protect your boys,

38:57.878 --> 39:00.297
but I have to protect mine.

39:00.381 --> 39:02.425
I have to be honest with him.

39:05.678 --> 39:08.514
Ugh. God, this is so fucked up.

39:11.809 --> 39:13.894
Have you told your boys about Ziggy?

39:14.937 --> 39:17.314
Not yet, no. I just...

39:19.859 --> 39:21.485
I will. I mean...

39:28.200 --> 39:29.493
Bonnie.

39:29.577 --> 39:30.995
- Hey.
- Hey.

39:31.078 --> 39:33.372
- Could you talk for a second?
- Sure.

39:33.456 --> 39:34.915
Um...

39:34.999 --> 39:40.254
This is in no way meant to blame you
or Nathan at all, for that matter,

39:40.337 --> 39:44.050
but that said, I just feel strongly
that Abigail come stay with me.

39:44.133 --> 39:46.594
Yeah,
she needs more than I can give her.

39:50.264 --> 39:52.475
What's going on?

39:52.558 --> 39:53.558
Are you okay?

39:54.727 --> 39:59.106
No, I'm not okay. I told you I wasn't okay.
I'm having a hard time with the whole thing.

40:01.192 --> 40:05.905
Sometimes I wake up at night in a sweat
with this feeling.

40:07.865 --> 40:10.409
It's gonna get us. It's gonna get us all.

40:11.744 --> 40:13.370
Who are you talking about?

40:15.122 --> 40:16.123
The lie.

40:18.793 --> 40:19.793
I gotta go.

40:23.380 --> 40:28.010
<i>♪ As I walk this land of broken dreams ♪</i>

40:28.094 --> 40:32.640
<i>♪ I have visions of many things ♪</i>

40:36.852 --> 40:38.270
You used to like that song.

40:38.354 --> 40:41.440
I used to like to sit on your face too.
You think that'll happen again?

40:44.276 --> 40:46.570
I mean, give me one fucking reason.

40:48.405 --> 40:49.448
I wanted a Gulfstream.

40:50.449 --> 40:53.160
- Ow! What the fuck?
- Fucking pitiful.

